HEADWORD: Wash stand
<hw>Wash stand</hw>. <def>In a stable or garage, a place in the floor
prepared so that carriages or automobiles may be washed there and the
water run off.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

